Assignment name  : capitalize_words
Expected files   : capitalize_words.c
Allowed functions: write
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Write a program that takes a string and capitalizes the first letter of each
word.

All other letters in the word must be changed to lowercase.

A word is a group of alphabetic characters. Any non-alphabetic character is
considered a separator.

The result must be followed by a newline.

If the number of parameters is not 1, the program displays only a newline.

Examples:

$> ./capitalize_words "hello world" | cat -e
Hello World$
$> ./capitalize_words "saLut, cOMment tu vas ?" | cat -e
Salut, Comment Tu Vas ?$
$> ./capitalize_words "42school-is_Cool" | cat -e
42School-Is_Cool$
$> ./capitalize_words "aBcDeF" | cat -e
Abcdef$
$> ./capitalize_words | cat -e
$
